field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Removed from vacuum: in air since labeling 19A28. Evans2 since early january.

notes: 01... 10 mV/s to +1.38 V vs RHE. Converges to approximately the expected 100 uA, but big overshoot at first. Looks like clear exchange! (link1) Evans7 Putting resistor up from 100 Ohm to 200 Ohm. Scan rate down to 5 mV/s. 02... This is a "control" which has been oxidized but not cycled. It actually also shows some exchange! But this is as expected since it started as metallic Ru... it would have taken up some 18-O. Can I get the 18-O out? I'm going to try doing it very elegantly for the article, sucking out the electrolyte, then putting in fresh electrolyte, redoing the exchange experiment, and then boom! CO to pull out the 18-O. 03... potentiostat crashes before I can put in CO. Have to repair channel. 04... Whoa, big cathodic displacement current and then decent CO oxidation activity while holding at +1.2 V vs RHE! This is unexpected. Also, m/z=46 to m/z=44 ratio seems to be diverging. Wierd. Ah, makes sense! It just reduced while at +1.2 V vs RHE. I need to put in CO at even more anodic if I want the reduction to be caused by the potential sweep. link4 05... accidently ended file, restarted. Left it cycling at 1 mV/s for the entire EC-MS meeting. WTF, the M46/M44 ratio never stabilizes! It does though change as a function of potential. Seems higher at higher potentials. Why??? (link5) QMS acquisition crashed, new file started 15:32:40 Changing scan rate to 10 mV/s, maxes out potentiostat. Turning resistance down to 100 Ohm. Did a bunch of stuff, but time response has gotten terrible, and all the gases seem mixed up somewhere. There's a bubble and I'm wasting my time. CO strip kind of works. Put in CO2 carrier gas before next sample to make sure I can measure the real isotopic ratio. Note: I had tons of CO2 in before with the Baisheng samples, so it's not that the chamber hadn't seen it before. It actually looks like about 0.8% rather than the expected 0.4% What on earth is up with this??? Evans2 06... Back to 200 Ohm. Evans2, a shitty sample from Choongman's first deposition, never labeled or otherwise treated, as a control. M46/M44 ratio matches "natural" ratio, which I still don't understand why isn't 0.4%. Maybe I'm not hitting the top of the peak, as Ib mentioned in the ECMS meeting as a possible reason for deviating M34/M32 ratio. I've had M15 and M26 with me the whole time, what a waste. New MS file 19:59:22 Evans8 07... Wow, an ugly set of bubbles. Stepped up to 1.39 V vs RHE when 1.38 didn't quite give the desired M34 signal/noise. But maybe it doesn't matter, since M34 noise is so small compared to M34. 08... Beautiful CO-extraction of 18-O after the OER experiment :D link6. I wonder if that dissolves the Ru, or reduces it? Collected electrolyte, will hopefully find out. New chip, since I know this one has a cracked carrier gas outlet, and I suspect old one for making bubble problems worse. (I'm not completely sure why I suspect this.) New chip is 14-C2. Old chip (5-F2) in "used for Ru" dish. Evans6 Evans6. Same as Evans8, but with no electrolyte extraction between first exchange and CO extraction Some hairy bubbles while mounting. Flowing through RE and CE doesn't work. Sucked out electrolyte, stored as Evans 6 OCV, filled up again. Looks much quieter this time, but M32 stignal still a bit high. Ahh, still some fucking hair! 09... Haha, wow, this is bloody miserable. Hairy-est one of these I've seen. There is exchange, but this is NOT my Science figure. Maybe it's possible to fix by subtracting a multiple of M28. Nope, definitely not (link7) There's a full fucking 10% M46 in the CO2 (link8). Not quite as good as Evans8. Looks like there might be an optimum potential for O extraction! 1.28 V vs RHE. Ahhh, not really. Looks like M46/M44 ratio increases whenever the potential moves. (link9) Or maybe, the higher I go, the more mass 46 I get out. Ah! Here's what it is: It's the fucking catalyst corroding. The O comes out as it dissolves and can react with CO2. Alright, this mystery is unsolved, but I don't want to stay here all fucking night. Purging out the CO and gtfo'ing. link1 (Evans9)
